{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dc3ccaf6-e0c2-482e-a9cc-cc15a96b642e","content":"I can help you analyze your .NET crash dump! None of my specialized skills cover dump *analysis* (only collection), but here's how to proceed:\n\n**Recommended tools for analyzing `.dmp` files:**\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform, easiest)\n   ```bash\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n   dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n   ```\n   Key commands inside the REPL:\n   - `clrstack` — managed call stack of the crashing thread\n   - `pe` — print the last exception\n   - `dumpheap -stat` — heap overview\n   - `threads` — list all threads\n   - `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` — inspect specific threads\n\n2. **`lldb` + SOS** (Linux, more powerful)\n\n3. **WinDbg + SOS** (Windows, full-featured)\n\n**To get started**, can you:\n- Share the path to your `.dmp` file (or upload it to this environment)?\n- Tell me which .NET version your app targets?\n\nI can then walk you through the analysis interactively using `dotnet-dump analyze`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c28513f5-e68e-4967-a99f-3670b81e1e3e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants to analyze it. Let me think about what tools and approaches are available.\n\nLooking at the available skills, I see:\n- `dump-collect` - but this is for *collecting* dumps, not analyzing them. The description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\"\n\nSo none of the available skills are appropriate for dump analysis. Let me provide guidance directly.\n\nFor analyzing .NET crash dumps, the main tools are:\n1. `dotnet-dump analyze` - cross-platform managed dump analysis\n\n\n2. WinDbg with SOS extension on Windows\n3. lldb with SOS on Linux/macOS\n\nSince we're likely on Linux, `dotnet-dump analyze` would be the best option. I should ask where the dump file is located and help them work through analyzing it with the appropriate tool.","outputTokens":534,"requestId":"7853:19764A:1EB4B82:22464E2:69FA9F2B"},"id":"b9d8b660-a53e-4cf6-aa4a-6ca06a5fe971","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:54:00.606Z","parentId":"e5378e46-4d5d-41d0-917e-f92fe57b4849"}
